### PATCH /api/me

**Auth:** JWT

**Description:** Partially update the caller's profile. Available to unapproved members during onboarding.

**Body** (all fields optional):

| Field | Type |
|-------|------|
| `name` | string (1–200) |
| `phone` | string (max 50) |
| `title`, `company`, `city` | string |
| `bio` | string (max 2000) |
| `photoUrl`, `linkedinUrl` | URL or `""` |
| `roleCategory` | string |
| `industries`, `lookingFor`, `canOffer` | string[] (max 20 each) |
| `currentGoal` | string (max 500) |
| `expoPushToken` | string |
| `smsConsent`, `emailConsent` | boolean |

**Example request:**

```bash
curl -X PATCH http://localhost:4000/api/me \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title": "CTO", "city": "Dallas"}'
```

**Success response (200):** Updated profile object (same shape as `GET /api/me`).

